parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling when Slowing Down or Shifting Gears
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling can cause the motorcycle to lose power and control, leading to accidents or injuries, especially when slowing down or approaching intersections.
symptoms: The engine stalls when slowing down
shifting gears
or pulling in the clutch
often without warning. The stalling may occur repeatedly
and the motorcycle may require multiple attempts to restart.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine when the clutch is engaged can cause the motorcycle to lose power and momentum, potentially leading to accidents, especially when slowing down or approaching intersections.
symptoms: The engine stalls when the clutch is pulled in
the motorcycle loses power
the engine cuts off
the motorcycle slows down unexpectedly
the engine restarts immediately after stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling issue can cause the motorcycle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of control, especially when approaching intersections or stop signs, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls or dies when downshifting
coasting
or coming to a stop
requiring the rider to restart the motorcycle
and potentially causing a safety hazard.
